Users can see a list of all active events:
- SELECT name FROM events WHERE active = true;

Users can see a list of all events near a given location (GPS) within 50 kilometers:
- SELECT name FROM events WHERE
    (SQRT(POW(lon_event - lon_user, 2) + POW(lat_event - lat_user, 2)) < 50)
    AND active = true;

Users can buy tickets for an event:
- INSERT INTO orders
    (customer_id)
    VALUES
    (<userID>)
    RETURNING id;
- INSERT INTO orderlines
    (order_id, event_id, tickets_adult, tickets_kid)
    VALUES
    (<^orderID>, <eventID>, <adultTickets>, <kidTickets>);

Customers can see a list of all bought tickets:
- SELECT id FROM orders WHERE customer_id = <userID>;
- SELECT * FROM orderlines WHERE order_id IN ^;

An administrator can see all events:
- SELECT name FROM events;

An administrator can add/update/delete events:
- INSERT INTO events
    (name, location, [description,] [active,] [availability,] price_adult, price_kid, [discount_req_adults,] [discount_req_kids,] [discount_percent])
    VALUES
    ('<name>', '<location>', ['<description>',] [<active>,] [<availability>,] <adultPrice>, <kidPrice>, [<discount_req_adults>,] [<discount_req_kids>,] [<discount_percent>]);
- UPDATE events
    SET
    <propertyName> = '<newValue>'
    WHERE
    id = <eventID>;
- DELETE FROM events
    WHERE
    id = <eventID>;

An administrator can see a list of all customers:
- SELECT name FROM users;
